R4 is H or alkyl;
R5 is:

each Ra, Rb, Rc, Rd, and Re is independently H or alkyl; or Rd and R1 taken together with the carbon atom to which they are attached form a carbocyclic ring; or Rc, Rd, and Re, taken together with the carbon atom to which they are attached, form a bicycloalkyl or tricycloalkyl ring;
R6, R7, and R8 are each independently H, F, Cl, Br, or alkyl;
R9 is H, alkyl, aryl, —C(═O)—R11, —C(═O)—OR11, —[C(R11)(R11)]s—C(═O)—OR11, —SO2R11, or —C(═O)N(R11)R11;
R10 is H, alkyl, or aryl;
each R11 is independently H or alkyl;
r is 0, 1, 2, or 3; and
s is 1, 2, 3, or 4;
provided that:
(1) when Rd and Re taken together with the carbon atom to which they are attached form a monocyclic carbocyclic ring, then Rc is alkyl or the monocyclic carbocyclic ring is an alkylcycloalkyl ring;
(2) at least two of Rc, Rd, and Re are other than H; and
